cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.DL 

This paper combines online data with traditional surveillance data to model the effect of mass media on the transmission of influenza. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy), and cs.DL (Machine Learning). However, given the focus on social media data and its impact on disease transmission, cs.SI and cs.SD are the most likely sub-categories.
